she 's right - it could happen to you this is an honest , funny , and sweet memoir of pregnancy and the first year as a parent . brockenbrough takes us along on her journey as she lives the ups and downs of life as a new parent . it 's sometimes funny , sometimes endearing , but always entertaining . brockenbrough is not as outrageous as jenny mccarthy , which is a good thing , because her book will appeal to everyone . it could be you in this book , for all intents and purposes , and reading someone else 's first experience with parenthood is sure to arm a new mom with insights and hope .